radiographic_examinations.findings: The appendix is dilated and fluid-filled measuring 1.0 cm with thickened and hyperemic walls. There is a trace amount of free fluid in the pelvis. Visualized lung fields are within normal limits with no evidence of pleural or pericardial effusion. Normal findings were noted in the liver, pancreas, spleen, adrenal glands, kidneys, stomach, small bowel, colon, rectum, urinary bladder, and reproductive organs. No lymphadenopathy or vascular abnormalities were observed. No evidence of worrisome osseous lesions or acute fracture.
